reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for the price
reviews.reviewText: When I first got the item I was planning on sending back immediately. Looked super cheap and flimsy and couldn’t get the boxes to stay together. Also the boxes are not clear more of a frost color. That’s not a big deal. But the instructions to assemble were hard to follow. I finally watched a review video on how to put them together and it was simple to follow. Recommend watching his video review. Boxes are nice for the price point. I bought the XXL boxes for my son. It is definitely wall to wall with his size 14 shoe. Some of the shoes are too big/bulky for the boxes but overall fits the majority of his men’s size 14.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better than expected
reviews.reviewText: I have been hesitant to buy sneaker boxes like this in the past. I was unsure of the overall style, stability and size. I am happy to report, I couldn't be happier. They look great, stack well and fit both low top and mids. The mids I did turn on thier side and back to front. Still looks great.Sneaker size 8M - 9M and 9W-10WShoe box size L*I Used tabs on the side to stack. Held well. Only one tab cracked, most likely user error.Would highly recommend if you want a trendy, stylish and affordable option for your shoe and sneaker storage/display.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: When I unpacked these, I was disappointed in the quality. They are very thin-not as I expected from the photos. However, after assembly, I think they will work quite well, if you don't plan on stacking them too high. I believe they will not hold up well with too much weight on top. They come flat. The sides must be bent into a “box” shape, and then the front and back are attached. Easy assembly. Doors are “hinged”. I have women’s size 9 shoes, and ordered the smaller size. But if you have high heeled shoes, I would order the larger size.

reviews.reviewText: I ordered the shoe boxes to organize some of my shoes that were not in boxes. The boxes are easy to assemble and to connect to other shoeboxes. However, sometimes the door disconnects from the hinges when you pull it open to remove your shoes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Plastic. Pictures might be deceiving
reviews.reviewText: The SEE SPRING Large 12 Pack Shoe Storage Box is a clear plastic stackable shoe organizer that can help you keep your closet organized and save space. Here's a review that includes both the pros and cons of this product:Pros:Space-saving: These shoe storage boxes are stackable, which means that you can store multiple pairs of shoes in a small amount of space. This is especially helpful if you have a small closet or limited storage space.Easy to see: The clear plastic design of the shoe boxes makes it easy to see what shoes are inside without having to open the box.Easy to clean: The plastic material is easy to wipe clean and is durable enough to last for a long time.Foldable: The shoe boxes can be easily folded flat when not in use, which makes them easy to store and transport.Cons:Limited size options: These shoe boxes only come in one size, which may not be suitable for larger shoes or boots.Durability: Some users have reported that the plastic material is not as durable as they would like and that the boxes can crack or break easily if not handled carefully.No air circulation: The boxes do not have any ventilation holes, which may cause shoes to become musty or develop an odor if left in the boxes for a long time.Overall, the SEE SPRING Large 12 Pack Shoe Storage Box is a good option for those looking for a space-saving and easy-to-use shoe organizer. While there are some cons to consider, the clear plastic design, ease of cleaning, and foldable design make these boxes a convenient and practical solution for organizing your shoes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works for me, but I want to be real…
reviews.reviewText: I gave this product 5 stars because it accomplished what I wanted to accomplish for a favorable price compared to research I’ve done on similar products. So for me, it works. For people interested in this product and reading reviews, I want to be helpful:Assembly: Requires patience, especially on the first couple. Not for those who easily get frustrated. While trying to assemble the first box, I thought for sure I would returning but I stuck with it, and they got easier as I went on. Took me an hour to assemble the 12 boxes and stack as shown in the pictures.Display: If you are looking to “display” your prized sneaker or heals collection, this is not the product as you can see from my images. The clear boxes are not so clear as you can see. Theres a cross web likely for sturdiness. Again, this was okay with me because I was simply trying to protect my shoes, and get them stacked rather the taking up space on the floor.Size: After opening the box and seeing the door size, I thought for sure I’d have to return. I missed the top to bottom size when determining whether or not to purchase, but it’s clearly in the product images, and it’s only 6” for the XL version (5” for the regular). My highest sneaks are Jordan 4s. These JUST fit and I had to put them in sideways through the door, then flip upright. I am not sure how tall high heals go, but take note if you wear them. My Timberlands and Nike ACGs will not fit in these.Takeaways: If you want to display your shoe collection, this is not for you. If you have shoes or sneakers over 6” tall, this is not for you. If you want to protect your shoes/sneakers completely, be able to stack them to save floor space, and are willing to take the time to assemble, this is a great cost effective solution.

Je suis surprise de la qualité du produit et de sa durabilité. Même si le plastique de la boîte apparaît mince, il est particulièrement solide et la transparence permet de voir les souliers ce qui est très pratique. Par ailleurs, le système pour faire le montage des boites est super facile même s’il faut quelques minutes pour figurer comment ça fonctionne. J’ai fait plusieurs recherches pour choisir ce système de rangement et je dois dire que le prix est raisonnable comparativement aux autres items identiques trouvés sur le site Amazon. Je suis très satisfaite du rapport qualité-prix. Important de savoir cependant que les boites « medium » ne permettent pas de mettre des souliers à talons hauts debout dans la boîte. Il faut alors les mettre de position couchée mais comme on dit, ça fait la job. À acheter de nouveau sans hésitations.

reviews.reviewTitle: Too tiny for Adults shoes,kids only
reviews.reviewText: The actual item and picture does not marry at all. Long process for return and I am still on it

I have so much love for these stackable shoe boxes! So easy to assemble and stack together, they have completely revamped my entryway! The shoe boxes also fit perfectly in an Ikea Kallax sideways and are great for having two-tier shelving for books and DVDs!

The plastic is not super clear like in the pictures. There's a pattern on it which I assume is to hide potential manufacturing defects in the finish.High top shoes don't fit standing up like in the pictures either, they need to be placed on their side to fit.That being said once assembled and stacked they look good and function well
